               <sense xml:id="Dmain" xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann"> <gramGrp> <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos> </gramGrp> <sense n="1" xml:id="D1"> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> occursus </quote></cit>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወፅአ፡ ለቀበላ፡ ዓሣ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="2 Par." loc="15,2">2 Par. 15,2</ref>; 2 <ref cRef="Par." loc="28,9">Par. 28,9</ref>; <ref cRef="Jes." loc="21,14">Jes. 21,14</ref> <lbl expand="varia lectio">var.</lbl>; <ref cRef="1 Thess." loc="4,17">1 Thess. 4,17</ref> ant; <ref cRef="Matth." loc="25,6">Matth. 25,6</ref>; hostilis: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለቀበላሆሙ፡ ለኢሎፍሊ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="1 Par." loc="14,8">1 Par. 14,8</ref>. 
</sense> <sense n="2" xml:id="D2"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቀበላ፡ ጾም፡</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> occursus </quote></cit> i.e. <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> initium jejunii </quote></cit> nominatur <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> dies jejunii quadragesimalis primus </quote></cit> (in ecclesia Romana: dies cinerum); in libris <cb n="0436" xml:id="c0436"/> de Comp. Eccl.; <ref cRef="Abush." loc="27 ">Abush. 27 </ref>et <ref cRef="Abush." loc="28">Abush. 28</ref>; <ref cRef="2 Cor." loc="11,3">2 Cor. 11,3</ref> in tit.; Vit. Sam., al. 
</sense> </sense>
               
            <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>qabbalā</quote></cit> <sense n="1" xml:id="T1"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቀበላ፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>qabbalā</quote></cit>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቅበላ፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>qǝbbalā</quote></cit> <bibl><ptr target="bm:Kasate1957DictAmh"/><citedRange unit="page"> 377b</citedRange></bibl> the Sunday before Lent <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማዕድ፡ ዘይሁብ፡ ንቡረ፡ እድ፡ ለ፸፡ ደብተራ፡ አልህምተ፡ በልደት፡ ፯፡ በጥምቀት፡ ፯፡ በቀበላ፡ ፯፡ በፋሲካ፡ ፯፡ በልደታ፡</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote>Repas que le nebura ed donne aux 70 dabtarā: 7 bœuf pour la Noël, 7 pour l’Epiphanie, 7 pour la qabbalā, 7 pour les Pâques</quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1909LiberT"/><citedRange unit="page"> 13 l. 1–2 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1910LiberV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 13 l. 27–29 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> 
</sense> <sense n="2" xml:id="T2"> <ptr target="#D2"/> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቀበላ፡ ጾም፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> qabbalā ṣom </quote></cit> ‘first week of Lent’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Kane1990DictAmhVol1"/><citedRange unit="page"> 766b</citedRange></bibl> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወአሜሃ፡ እምድኅረ፡ ቀበላ፡ ጾም፡ አርትዓ፡ ፍኖቶ፡ መንገለ፡ ወጅ፡ ከመ፡ ይሖር፡ በጥራሞራ።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote> Alors, aprés le qabalā du Carême, le roi se dirigea vers le Waǧ, pour aller à Baṭerāmorā </quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1907SarsaDengel"/><citedRange unit="page"> 26 l. 18–19 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1907SarsaDengelV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 30 l. 36, 31 l. 1 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> 
</sense> <sense n="G" xml:id="TG"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቀበላ፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>qabbalā</quote></cit> (terme liturgique) dimanche que précède la <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote>feria secunda</quote></cit> de la première semaine du Carême; ce mot désigne aussi <cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote>l’avant-veille du Carême</quote></cit> ou ‘samedi; il peut encore s’appliquer aux deux et même aux trois jours précédant d’autres jeûnes que le Carême, à condition que ceux-ci soient d’assez longue durée, v.g.: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጾመ፡ ልደት፡</foreign> (<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote>le jeûne de Noël</quote></cit>), <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጾመ፡ ቍስቋም፡</foreign> (<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote>le jeûne de Quesquâm</quote></cit>), <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጾመ፡ ፍልሰታ፡</foreign> (<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote>le jeûne de l’Assomption</quote></cit>). ― Il convient de signaler la différence sémantique entre le mot isolé <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቀበላ፡</foreign> (sens précisé plus haut) et l’expression <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቀበላ፡ ጾም፡</foreign> la plus fréquemment employée pour désigner la <cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote>première semaine du Carême</quote></cit>. ― Dans les expressions <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቀበላ፡ ጾም፡</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጾመ፡ ድጓ፡</foreign> et <foreign xml:lang="gez">በአተ፡ ጾም፡</foreign>, le vocable <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጾም፡</foreign> présente non le sens général de <cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote>jeûne</quote></cit>, mais désigne surtout <cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote>le Carême</quote></cit>. C’est ainsi qu’on recontre fréquemment dans les ‘Tārik’ (Chroniques) la phrase suivante: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወዐለ፡ ንጉሥ፡ በህየ፡ በዓለ፡ ቀበላ፡ ጾም።</foreign> <lb/>
 <bibl><ptr target="bm:Grebaut1952SuppLexicon"/><citedRange unit="page"> 175–176</citedRange></bibl> 
</sense> <sense n="L" xml:id="TL"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቀበላ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>qabbalā</quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>meeting</quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>encounter</quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>reception</quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>offering</quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>Saturday before Lent</quote></cit> (two and tree days), <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>period before any fast of a longer duration</quote></cit> <lb/>
